                            <comment id="15018314" author="jahewson" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2015 16:51:25 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Effect happens with a real printer, but not when printing to PDF or to XPS.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That most likely means it&apos;s an issue with the user&apos;s printer configuration. We can only influence the output as seen in the PDF/XPS, so I don&apos;t see what we&apos;re supposed to do about this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15369060" author="tilman" created="Sat, 9 Jul 2016 11:03:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-3117&quot; title=&quot;Left margin cut off when printing&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-3117&quot;&gt;PDFBOX-3117&lt;/a&gt;.pdf is the file I created.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-3117&quot; title=&quot;Left margin cut off when printing&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-3117&quot;&gt;PDFBOX-3117&lt;/a&gt;-1468001565.pdf is a label from Frank Malenfant who created it to be printed on a Zebra ZT230 label printer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Both files are cut off at the left when printing on my HP1020 printer on ordinary A4 paper with this code:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;                PrinterJob job = PrinterJob.getPrinterJob();
                job.setPageable(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; PDFPageable(document, Orientation.PORTRAIT, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;, 0));
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (job.printDialog())
                {
                    job.print();
                }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15369061" author="tilman" created="Sat, 9 Jul 2016 11:32:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;When commenting out the workaround in &lt;tt&gt;PDFPageable.getPageFormat()&lt;/tt&gt;, the label is printed with almost nothing cut off, my file is unchanged. (but that one has only 1cm cut off, but Acrobat does the same when printing to &quot;actual size&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17854743" author="tilman" created="Thu, 13 Jun 2024 12:58:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Back to this because of this question:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://lists.apache.org/thread/12s9tc93ofgmjfq1dpqfps9p725l0wwr&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://lists.apache.org/thread/12s9tc93ofgmjfq1dpqfps9p725l0wwr&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m adding a check to disable centering if the translation has a negative value. Landscape labels can be printed without rotation if PORTRAIT is used as a parameter.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17854745" author="jira-bot" created="Thu, 13 Jun 2024 13:04:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1918293 from Tilman Hausherr in branch &apos;pdfbox/branches/2.0&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
